“docks” includes basins, locks, cuts, entrances, graving-docks, keel-
blocks,  inclined-planes,  slipways,  gridirons,  quays,  warehouses  and 
other works and things appertaining to docks;

“licensed  warehouse”  means  a  warehouse  or  other  place  licensed 
for  the  warehousing  of  dutiable  goods  under  section  65  of  the 
Customs Act 1967 [Act 235];

“Minister”  and  “Minister  of  Finance”  mean  the  Federal  Ministers 
charged  with  responsibility  respectively  for  ports  and  harbours,  and 
for finance;

“pier” includes a stage, stairs, a landing-place, landing-stage, jetty, 
floating  barge  or  pontoon  and  a  bridge,  and  other  works  connected 
therewith;

“vehicle”  includes  a  carriage  travelling  on  its  own  wheels  or 
runners  and  used  or  intended  to  be  used  for  the  conveyance  or 
carriage of persons, animals or goods;

to  purchase  or  otherwise  acquire  or  construct,  and  to 
